{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://aureline.dev/schemas/companion/ship-session-follow-and-incident-awareness-surfaces-with-bounded-read-write-scope-and-stale-state-honesty.schema.json",
  "title": "Aureline companion session-follow and incident-awareness surfaces with bounded read/write scope and stale-state honesty",
  "description": "Export-safe packet for the companion surfaces that follow an active desktop session and stay aware of incidents, plus the single bounded light-edit surface that may write. It projects three surfaces — session-follow, incident-awareness, and bounded light-edit — each inheriting qualification from a frozen M5 companion-matrix lane, and gives every item an exact desktop handoff. Bounded read/write scope: session-follow and incident-awareness are read-only; only the bounded light-edit surface may write, and only via a host-approved relay. Stale-state honesty: every item carries a freshness state, stale or unknown freshness is always labeled, and a degraded item is never shown as live. Degraded state (relay unavailable, stale proof, inactive host, narrowed trust, lost incident attribution, narrowed upstream lane, unresolved handoff, downgraded freshness) is labeled rather than hidden. Credential bodies, raw provider payloads, and raw session or incident bodies never cross this boundary.",
